Package database

Class ServicePointConfig

java.lang.Object
database.ServicePointConfig
public class ServicePointConfig extends Object
Represents the configuration for a service point at an airport. This includes details like the type of service point (e.g., CHECKIN, SECURITY), the number of servers, mean service time, and parameters for the service time distribution.

    • ServicePointConfig

      public ServicePointConfig(org.bson.types.ObjectId id, org.bson.types.ObjectId airportId, String pointType, int numberOfServers, double meanServiceTime, String distributionType, Double param1, Double param2)
      Constructs a ServicePointConfig object with specified parameters.
      Parameters:
      id - The unique identifier of the service point configuration.
      airportId - The identifier of the airport this configuration belongs to.
      pointType - The type of the service point (e.g., "CHECKIN", "SECURITY").
      numberOfServers - The number of servers available at this service point.
      meanServiceTime - The mean service time for this service point.
      distributionType - The type of probability distribution for service times (e.g., "NORMAL", "UNIFORM").
      param1 - The first parameter for the distribution (e.g., standard deviation for NORMAL, min for UNIFORM).
      param2 - The second parameter for the distribution (e.g., max for UNIFORM).
